comments.body:
We tested your issue using the latest Appcelerator version. Not sure if this is still an issue for you. It doesn't appear to be based on our latest tests.

Please follow the steps below and let us know.

1. Check if Java JDK is installed: Java --version(if not installed, you can download it from [here|http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html] ).
2. Ensure that you have Node.JS installed: node --version (if not installed then you can download it from [here|http://nodejs.org/download/])
3. Install the Appcelerator CLI: npm install appcelerator -g
4. appc setup
Login to Appcelerator Studio from terminal using below command and then open your Studio:
appc login
If the problem still persist then:
Uninstall SDK:
appc ti sdk uninstall (SDK version)
Install SDK:
appc ti sdk install latest or
appc use latest
